ituational.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Sure.<br>
<br>
First, charmed pets have always been potentially more powerful than summoned pets.   I am certain that there will be charmable elemental NPCs more powerful than our summoned pets.  You might well enter an area knowing that you want to charm an elemental for your pet.<br>
<br>
Second, under some circumstances, charm is a better crowd control mechanicism than mezz.  There are mobs that cannot be mezzed, for example, but can be charmed.  Likewise, there may be summoned creatures that cannot be mezzed, but can be charmed.<br>
<br>
There are quest hand in mobs that must be charmed.<br>
<br>
Charm allows you to move a mob.  For example, you could use charm to pull.<br>
<br>
Charm allows you to buff mobs.  This might be used to grief others on PvP servers.<br>
<br>
I am not even an enchanter, nor have I ever played one, but these are just off the top of my head what I have seen or read about.<br>
<br>
I am sure a more knowledgeable person can suggest more.<br>
<br>
