<br>
There are two problems with this....<br>
<br>
If you are fighting a mob and charm breaks, now you have two mobs on you. <br>
<br>
Ok lets say for arguments sake you are able to channel a mezz on both. I was told this mezz last for 45secs. So that means by the time that you mezz the second mob depending on perfect channeling and getting off mezzes without a hitch by the time your spell icons refresh from mezzing the second target you now have 38secs left before the first mob's mezz wears off.<br>
<br>
You can not charm a mezzed NPC. Mezz must be broken before you can re-charm. Charm is a hellish aggro so summoning your own pet isn't going to free you from aggro. Also if these charm mobs are on par with shimmering rockfiends in the Grey you have a problem. Those things will chew out a GV pet in secs with little problem. Your only options really is to run for the zone or to risk trying to re-charm your mob that is doubling for 200.<br>
<br>
I see the charming ability as a useful skill in a group. Where a healer is present and you can take hits without fear of death. Without a shield of auras type item and a zland heart I wouldn't dare try this solo. Verant needs to add elemental stun then this would be a useful solo skill. Without stun or root charm soloing is going to cause alot of zones to be littered with dead mage corpses.<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
