<br>
enchanter: charm everything<br>
pbae stun: charm breaks stun both mez one stun again charm other resume fighting. <br>
single target stun: stun second then try and channel charm on 1st. <br>
root: root second mob while fighting charmed. charm breaks root 1st then recharm at leisure. <br>
mez: mez 2nd: try and channel to recharm 1st. <br>
rune: take a few hits while mobs are beating on ya during recharm process.<br>
Fear: fear one mob deal with other. <br>
<br>
bards: everything<br>
snare: run a bit to get time to cast charm again resume fight. <br>
fear: see enchanter fear<br>
cast charm while running:<br>
single target stun:<br>
<br>
<br>
necro: undead charm<br>
Fear: see enchanter fear<br>
root: see enchanter root<br>
feign death: fall to ground mobs dont even realize your their stand recharm and sic pet on mob again. <br>
snare: see bard snare<br>
screaming terror: see mez. <br>
skin: see enchanter rune<br>
harmsheild: 18 seconds to figure out what you want to do<br>
<br>
druid : animal charm<br>
root: see enchanter root<br>
snare: see necro snare.<br>
succor: remove self from hate list. <br>
fear: see enchanter fear.<br>
<br>
mages: proposed elemental charm<br>
mez: see enchanter mez.<br>
pet in your backpack: aa ablitily of pet suspension if it allows you to charm or resummon pets while one is suspended. also dependant on time to unsuspend.<br>
<br>
basically we are ill equipped to deal with the downside of charm in that once charm breaks we are defenseless. period end of story. all other charm classes (including the weak shammie charms) have secondary skills that suppliment the charm. stuns for the enchanter help a ton (they are the charm specialists) fd for the necro along with the skins. bards casting while running and druids 10 minute ensnare before ya charm the mob makes all the difference in the wolrd.  mages well we run like hell either to the zone or to our corpse. <br>
<br>
and i highly doubt we will be able to have our pet up and charm a mob at the same time. no other class can. <br>
<br>
im all about the mez assuming that there are mobs to use it on. but charm more than likely will never even be purchased much less put at the back of my spellbook. <br>
